&lt;p&gt;Kettle is a team of passionate, fearless creatives focused on delivering great products, redefining best-practices, and providing new opportunities for our clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for our first Director, Creative Operations to partner with our Creative, Production, Technology and Account leaders to help define and optimize the processes that will help us succeed as we continue to grow. In this internally focused role, you’ll establish structure and bring clarity to our team that turns creative ideas into reality in the marketing communications space. This is an exciting opportunity for an entrepreneurial individual with a passion for and background in problem solving and operations within a creative environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates should have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience in a digital, creative agency and/or fast-paced creative tech organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A background in Production, Program Management, Creative Resourcing, Creative Operations, and/or People Operations, preferably in a growth-oriented environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A problem solver mentality, with the ability to break down complex problems into simple steps and actions, and create streamlined processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and listening skills, and the ability to influence others at various levels and on cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience operating at 10,000 feet, and the ability to sit down with creatives and producers to solve day-to-day challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work West Coast hours, and/or be located in the SF or LA area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’d like to know that you can:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead and manage projects in the following areas:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operations and Resource Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the day-to-day operations of the creative team, ensuring resources are allocated effectively, timelines are met, and projects are delivered on time and on budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously evaluate and refine creative processes to ensure efficiency, scalability, and adaptability across brands and projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI implementation and adoption in workflows and process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and manage dashboards and data for process analysis and improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document and think critically about ways of working and collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate and lead the onboarding of new Kettle creatives, optimizing and systematizing that process to set new hires up for success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team and Culture Building&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help shape and communicate team mission, vision, and values development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the champion for team rituals, events, and meetings strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;With HR and Talent and key discipline leads, develop leveling and career pathways progression and documentation, hiring and onboarding processes, and management standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business and Strategy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in quarterly and yearly planning discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand team financials, ensuring that resources are allocated effectively to meet strategic goals within budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to offerings definition and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The target range of base compensation for this role is $150k-180k. Actual compensation is influenced by a wide array of factors including but not limited to skill set, level of experience, and location.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kettle is a team of passionate, fearless creatives focused on delivering great products, redefining best-practices, and providing new opportunities for our clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Director of Product Design to join and help lead the Product team. In this role, you’ll set product vision, design new features, and enhance existing ones while establishing scalable UX/UI patterns across platforms. Our Directors are designers and doers, both leading and managing, and contributing directly to the work as the most senior practitioner on the team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates should have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive Product Design and interaction experience in either agency or related environments designing iOS and Android native applications, websites, and internal tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design Leadership experience across the product design lifecycle, including experience leading both UX and UI design workstreams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A clear communication style, with proven experience collaborating with senior level clients and presenting to executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience delivering user-focused solutions across a range of categories (Financial Services, Telecomm, Consumer tech, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in agile product design/development models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing and mentoring Junior to Senior level product designers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing AI-enabled features, vibe coding, and rapid prototyping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’d like to know that you can:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide high-level strategic decisions around product design and experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the entire product lifecycle from start to finish — starting with defining IA, user journey, wireframes, to designing user interactions and handoff to development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balance leadership of the team with hands-on design work, guiding projects towards design excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the IxD stream of work on projects, understanding how to break larger projects down into smaller tracts to handoff to designers and bring learnings from one work stream to another.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with teammates of different disciplines including Strategy, Production, and Development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong client relationships with a solid understanding of their business needs, goals, and how those intersect with the consumer’s experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adapt to different working styles and processes, from quick turn optimization to blue sky visioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and mentor designers of all levels, helping them chart their career path and provide opportunities to grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The target range of base compensation for this role is $180k-$215k. Actual compensation is influenced by a wide array of factors including but not limited to skill set, level of experience, and location.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kettle is a team of passionate creatives focused on delivering great products, redefining best-practices, and providing new opportunities for our clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for freelance Production Designers to join our largest account for a global creative tech organization. In this role, you’ll create pixel-perfect digital design files in partnership with our Visual Designers and Art Directors, and the wider creative and production teams. Our Production Design team is a highly skilled, fast, and flexible group dedicated to design excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires the team to be onsite 5 days per week in Sunnyvale, Playa Vista, or Austin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates should have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced knowledge of Figma/Sketch and Adobe Photoshop; bonus if you have experience in building responsive websites or working with HTML syntax&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive communication skills, and the ability to work on multiple projects with large and variable teams simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to follow design systems and adapt to varying requirements technical specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A portfolio of strong digital design, with examples of banners, emails, and landing pages at various viewport sizes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’d like to know that you can:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean up design files and convert designs into templates at various viewport sizes based off of an original design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce a large volume of banners, emails, and landing pages at a consistent pace, with minimal direction and oversight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure every pixel is in the correct place, all assets are linked, layers and groups are organized, and files are named correctly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidently update existing designs not requiring creative input (glyphs, icons, copy, image swaps)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create spec documentation so other teams understand design intent&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide your team to create own-able experiences for the client through simple and relevant concepts, clear innovative UX, beautiful art direction and on-point tone &amp;amp; voice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The compensation range for this role is $7,500 - 10,500 monthly. Actual compensation is influenced by a wide array of factors including but not limited to skill set, level of experience, and location.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At Kettle, we build digital experiences that are both functional and emotional. We believe the future of digital should feel incredibly personal, and that takes teams who know how to move quickly, collaborate deeply, and deliver exceptional work at a high level of craft.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Recruiter to join our growing team. This role will partner closely with our Director of Talent Acquisition and network recruiters to fill roles for our Creative, Production, Technology, Strategy, and Operations partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role for someone who loves building relationships with hiring teams and candidates in support of a fast-paced creative organization. Our ideal candidate is a recruiting generalist who brings a thoughtful, can-do attitude, excellent communication skills, and the ability to navigate fast-moving environments with calm, clarity, and sound judgment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates should have:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A flexible and proactive attitude with a positive, solution-focused mindset&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional organizational skills and a process-driven mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and negotiation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience closing junior to senior level positions, and the ability to carry the conversation with hiring managers and leadership teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort managing multiple priorities and pivoting as needs change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience sourcing and advocating for diversity, equity, and inclusion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work West Coast hours, or be based on the West Coast&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5+ years as a Recruiter in a digital agency or in-house creative environment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’d like to know that you can:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage end to end recruitment for assigned roles from hiring manager brief to candidate sourcing and assessment through offer negotiation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with hiring managers to understand ideal candidate profiles for current and future business needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide candidates and hiring managers through the recruitment process keeping everyone updated and engaged along the way&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track candidates in Greenhouse to ensure accurate and up to date records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively build a pipeline of candidates for current and future roles&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide a best in class candidate experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source and engage with amazing people by leveraging conventional and unconventional methods to find the best candidates out there&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The target range of base compensation for this role is $85,000 - $115,000, and spans multiple levels. Actual compensation is influenced by a wide array of factors including but not limited to skill set, level of experience, and location.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kettle is a team of passionate, fearless creatives focused on delivering great products, redefining best-practices, and providing new opportunities for our clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for our first Senior Creator. This is a rare one. As a Creator at Kettle, you&#39;ll own the full arc of social content — from the spark of an idea to the final frame. You&#39;ll concept, pitch, shoot, art direct, produce, edit, write, and animate. All of it, for a legacy American clothing and accessories retailer. We&#39;re not looking for someone who does one thing well. We&#39;re looking for someone who does everything incredibly well — and has the aesthetic and experience to prove it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates should have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience creating content for brands, agencies, or both — with a portfolio (can be a website or your IG) that shows range, craft, and a genuine point of view&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A demonstrably strong aesthetic — your Instagram, TikTok, or portfolio should speak for itself before you say a word&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep passion for fashion, style, and consumer culture; you follow the space closely and it shows in your work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on production skills: you&#39;re comfortable behind a DSLR camera or your phone, in a prop shop, and on a set you built yourself&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency and experience in editing (Premiere Pro), graphic design (Adobe suite), motion graphics (After Effects), deck design (Figma, Keynote)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to write — not just captions, but ideas: concepts, scripts, creative rationale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience presenting and selling creative to clients; you can walk a room through an idea and make them believe in it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative instinct — you know when to lead and when to build on someone else&#39;s spark. You’re comfortable receiving feedback on your ideas, pivoting, taking others ideas and running with them, brainstorming, and receiving creative direction from your leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’d like to know that you can:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conceive original social content ideas for our fashion client — and sell them through directly to clients with confidence and creative conviction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own production start to finish: prop, style, and art direct shoots; operate camera; capture stills and video; and deliver polished, platform-ready content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Edit your own footage — short-form video, Reels, TikToks — with a sharp eye for pacing, rhythm, and visual storytelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build motion graphics and animated elements that elevate content beyond the standard social post&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write copy that is on-brand and platform-specific: captions, scripts, on-screen text, deck copy, and anything else the idea needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop multi-platform content systems — not just one-offs, but cohesive creative content series concepts that works across multiple social platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with strategists and creative leads to translate briefs into creative concepts that resonate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay ahead of platform trends, aesthetic shifts, and cultural moments in fashion and lifestyle — and bring that fluency into every brief&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The target range of base compensation for this role is $70,000 - 85,000. Actual compensation is influenced by a wide array of factors including but not limited to skill set, level of experience, and location.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kettle is a team of passionate, fearless creatives focused on delivering great products, redefining best-practices, and providing new opportunities for our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Producer to manage the day-to-day production of digital projects for a leading creative tech brand. You’ll be responsible for managing projects from coordination to delivery, while ensuring smooth communication between teams and clients. You will report to an EP, and independently drive a work stream with medium to large sized projects. This role requires long term planning, tactical execution, organization, process definition, relationship-building and attention to detail to ensure timely and high-quality deliverables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires you to be on-site in the Austin office up to 5x per week, depending on the project. There is some flex at other times during the year for hybrid work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience managing large digital projects, ideally in a creative agency or in-house marketing department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience managing production workflows, including resource allocation, scheduling, and coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and multitasking skills to manage day-to-day project needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills with an ability to liaise between internal teams and clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing digital product projects, such as the development of marketing tools, websites and/or apps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to meet deadlines and manage multiple projects simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A keen interest in AI and automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage daily project operations, including scheduling, resource coordination, ticket generation/delegation/tracking and team task assignments to ensure timely execution&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own multiple .com, digital/social advertising and digital product development tracks of work independently, ensuring they are delivered on time, within scope, and exceeding client expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage client communications, providing updates and ensuring that deliverables meet client expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track project progress, ensuring that tasks stay on schedule and adjusting plans as necessary to address delays or issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run quality control, ensuring all work is reviewed and meets both creative and technical standards before moving to the next phase of production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute process, while maintaining process documentation, training other team members and pivoting as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor other Producers with guidance and ensure alignment across all tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The target range of base compensation for this role is $110k-$150k. Actual compensation is influenced by a wide array of factors including but not limited to skill set, level of experience, and location.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
